criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  male or female

          -  13-18 years-old

          -  resident of Colorado

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  weigh less than 88 pounds or have a BMI% rank of <10% for age and sex;

          -  have a physician's diagnosis of metabolic syndrome or diabetes (Type 1 or 2);

          -  have a physician's diagnosis of anorexia nervosa or bulimia nervosa;

          -  currently taking anti-psychotic medications (not including anti-depressant or anti-
             anxiety medications);

          -  have a non-MRI safe device (e.g. pacemaker or defibrillator) or metal in the body
             (e.g. metal pins, shrapnel);

          -  experience symptoms of claustrophobia when in small or closed-off places;

          -  are pregnant or plan to become pregnant
